The paper deals with modal logics for reasoning about truth, belief, and knowledge, which are topics that are commonly studied in the field of logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the adoption of epistemic principles, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of algebraic semantics and relational semantics also suggests a connection to the fields of logic and computer science, particularly in the areas of algebraic logic (cs.LG), programming languages (cs.PL), and concurrency theory (cs.CC).
